Definition: an order to an offending party to rid itself of property
Example: it has the purpose of depriving the defendant of the gains of wrongful behavior; the court found divestiture to be necessary in preventing a monopoly
Synonyms: verb, possession, divest, court_order, noun, group, law, c, an, order, to, offending, party, rid, itself, of, property, it, has, the, purpose, depriving, defendant, gains, wrongful, behavior, court, found, be, necessary, in, preventing, a, monopoly
Category: noun.communication
